  "text": "A relaying strategy which allows to fulfill these requirements is compute-and-forward, which was introduced by Nazer and Gastpar in [CITATION_1] . The compute-and-forward framework is based on nested lattice codes and therefore uses structured codes instead of random coding. This allows to exploit the structure at the relay such that the relay can often recover an equation of messages at a higher rate than any individual message. As we will see later, the rates are highest when the equation coefficients closely approximate the channel coefficients. Due to space limitations we do not provide details about compute-and-forward in this paper and instead want to refer the reader to [CITATION_2] for details and to [CITATION_3] for an overview and a comparison to other schemes.",
